## Anti-Patterns

Do NOT:
- Generate placeholder text like "[description here]" or "[TBD]"
- Write generic requirements that could apply to any service
- Skip acceptance scenarios for user stories
- Use vague success criteria without measurable thresholds
- Copy requirements from other services without adaptation

## Quality Example

Good FR: "FR-001: System MUST validate email format using RFC 5322 and return 422 with field-level error details"
Bad FR: "FR-001: System should validate input appropriately"
